[[File:Higurashimon.JPG|thumb|right|The south gate of Yusuhara Shrine is called ''Higurashimon'']] {{nihongo|Yusuhara Hachiman-gū|柞原八幡宮||}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Oita, Oita]] on the island of [[Kyushu]].
Yusuhara was the chief Shinto shrine (''[[ichinomiya]]'') of the old [[Bungo Province]]. It serves today as one of the ''ichinomiya'' of [[Niigata Prefecture]]. <ref>[http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/images/uploads/EOS070712Ab.pdf "Nationwide List of ''Ichinomiya''," p. 3]; retrieved 2012-10-25.</ref>
==Related pages== * [[List of Shinto shrines in Japan]] * [[Modern system of ranked Shinto Shrines]]
==References== {{reflist}}
==External links == {{Commons category-inline|Yusuhara Hachimangu}}
